00:00:43.494 --> 00:00:47.289
Looking at this picture.
I know you might be thinkin':

3
00:00:47.373 --> 00:00:50.626
"Sure looks like a lonely place to be.
way up there".

4
00:00:50.709 --> 00:00:53.587
If indeed you were. I'd have to disagree.

5
00:00:53.629 --> 00:00:58.676
Truth is. when you stop to ponder it.
there's really no such thing as a lonely place.

6
00:00:58.759 --> 00:01:02.137
just lonely people. That's what I believe.

7
00:01:07.184 --> 00:01:12.940
You can be lonely any place:
up on a rooftop. at a big family shindig.

8
00:01:13.023 --> 00:01:16.986
in a football stadium.
with 60. 000 other humans all around.

9
00:01:17.069 --> 00:01:21.031
or even in a small town.
like Shelbyville. Indiana.

10
00:01:22.032 --> 00:01:24.869
Now. I'm not sayin'
there's anything wrong with it.

11
00:01:24.952 --> 00:01:29.707
In fact. loneliness is what ensures
the propagation of our species.

12
00:01:29.790 --> 00:01:32.459
I think that's why most people get married.

13
00:01:32.543 --> 00:01:36.088
Because they're lonely.
horny or out of money.

14
00:01:36.171 --> 00:01:39.466
But mostly cos they're just damn lonely.

15
00:01:40.467 --> 00:01:43.345
Of course. that is one hell
of a milk-toast reason

16
00:01:43.429 --> 00:01:47.558
to link up with one person
for the rest of your existence.

17
00:01:53.898 --> 00:01:58.652
But people do it every day.
They give in to their loneliness.

18
00:01:58.736 --> 00:02:02.406
And the next thing they know.
they're trapped.

19
00:02:05.367 --> 00:02:09.914
Perhaps I'm being too picky.
I talked to this counsellor once.

20
00:02:09.997 --> 00:02:12.750
He told me that the fact
I was raised in an orphanage

21
00:02:12.833 --> 00:02:17.755
has rendered me afraid of abandonment.
and therefore fearful of commitment.

22
00:02:17.838 --> 00:02:21.300
Now. you can tell by my tone.
I don't think much of his opinion.

23
00:02:21.383 --> 00:02:26.889
I'm ready to commit. just as soon as I find
that one woman I can't live without.

24
00:02:26.972 --> 00:02:31.769
That one woman that gives
me goose bumps all over.

25
00:02:31.852 --> 00:02:36.941
I simply refuse to settle for anything less.
like most people seem to do.

26
00:02:37.024 --> 00:02:39.568
Like my boss. Larry.

27
00:02:41.028 --> 00:02:43.113
Be a sport. will ya?

28
00:02:43.197 --> 00:02:47.993
I missed Ruthie's birthday dinner last night
and she's makin' my life hell in a handbasket.

29
00:02:48.077 --> 00:02:52.498
I know she'll go easier on me if you're there.
Come on now. Gilly. Do me this.

30
00:02:52.581 --> 00:02:56.794
- Bring her a puppy. Larry. She'll love that.
- What the hell is this?

31
00:02:56.835 --> 00:02:59.296
It's a Russian Pomeranian. Larry.

32
00:02:59.380 --> 00:03:02.466
Nah. I don't wanna put
any American dogs outta work.

33
00:03:02.550 --> 00:03:05.594
Come on now. Gilly.
Be a friend. Come on over.

34
00:03:05.970 --> 00:03:08.931
- I don't know. Larry. Last time I...
- Thanks. buddy.

35
00:03:09.014 --> 00:03:13.894
A slice of family life and home cookin' will
do your heart good. Bring some wine coolers.

36
00:03:14.019 --> 00:03:16.063
We'll make it a wingding.

37
00:03:19.900 --> 00:03:21.986
This is fine cuisine. Mrs P.

38
00:03:22.069 --> 00:03:24.113
It's takeout. Gilly.

39
00:03:24.947 --> 00:03:27.074
From Pizza Hut.

40
00:03:27.950 --> 00:03:31.579
- Larry hates my cooking.
- That's not true. Ruthie. You know I...

41
00:03:31.662 --> 00:03:36.417
- That's why he never comes home for dinner.
- I'm out there busting my ass.

42
00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:41.380
If you're busting your ass. how come
it's the size of a goddamn beanbag chair?

43
00:03:42.506 --> 00:03:47.678
If you put out once in a while. maybe I
wouldn't be seeking carnal pleasure in food.

44
00:03:47.761 --> 00:03:50.055
All right! Call me old-fashioned.

45
00:03:50.180 --> 00:03:53.851
but I don't think a child should be made
to picture her parents humping.

46
00:03:53.934 --> 00:03:57.021
- I don't tell you about my sex life.
- You're not having sex.

47
00:03:57.104 --> 00:04:01.483
- Are you having sex?
- Cher. tell Daddy you're kidding.

48
00:04:01.567 --> 00:04:05.237
She's kidding.
She doesn't even have a boyfriend.

49
00:04:05.321 --> 00:04:09.116
You don't need to have a boyfriend
to be having sex.

50
00:04:09.742 --> 00:04:14.455
I'm just saying that a boy doesn't have
to be a friend to be nibbling my package.

51
00:04:14.538 --> 00:04:18.083
- What? Are you...
- I think she's saying she's a whore. Pop.

52
00:04:18.167 --> 00:04:21.253
- Buddy!
- Pervert! I am not.

53
00:04:22.171 --> 00:04:24.215
I'm just popular.

54
00:04:24.965 --> 00:04:27.134
Like Gilly here.

55
00:04:27.218 --> 00:04:30.554
He doesn't have a girlfriend.
but I'll bet he's having sex.

56
00:04:30.638 --> 00:04:33.015
Well. occasionally. sure. but...

57
00:04:37.853 --> 00:04:41.649
Well. ultimately I believe in
waiting till one is married before...

58
00:04:41.732 --> 00:04:46.445
How come you don't have a girlfriend? Dad
says you're confused about your sexuality.

59
00:04:46.528 --> 00:04:50.407
- No. I never said that.
- I believe the term he used was "fagnostic".

60
00:04:50.491 --> 00:04:52.326
- Right. Fagnostic.
- Larry!

61
00:04:52.409 --> 00:04:55.287
- That's it! Go to your room. you two!
- What? Why?

62
00:04:55.412 --> 00:04:57.498
She's just repeating what you said.

63
00:04:57.581 --> 00:05:01.252
You always take her side!
You let her get her ears pierced.

64
00:05:01.335 --> 00:05:05.631
- You try to stop her!
- I got my ears pierced because I like it. OK?

65
00:05:05.714 --> 00:05:09.218
And I got these pierced because I hate you!

66
00:05:10.261 --> 00:05:12.513
Hey. that was you on the Internet!

67
00:05:19.562 --> 00:05:22.231
I am sick of bein' treated
like dirty bath water.

68
00:05:22.314 --> 00:05:28.195
I chase poodles all day so she can drive
around in a brand-new Saturn. Fully loaded!

69
00:05:28.279 --> 00:05:30.364
The usual. hon.

70
00:05:31.407 --> 00:05:36.537
This kinda thing makes a man wanna
bludgeon his family and get drunk.

71
00:05:36.662 --> 00:05:42.668
That's pretty serious talk. Larry. Maybe you
should speak to a professional about this.

72
00:05:42.751 --> 00:05:44.837
You mean a hit man?

73
00:05:44.920 --> 00:05:49.216
No. man. That's the easiest
way to get caught.

74
00:05:51.802 --> 00:05:56.140
- Unless you did it.
- I was talkin' about a shrink. Larry.

75
00:05:56.223 --> 00:05:59.435
Get real. man. That's for crazy people.

76
00:06:03.063 --> 00:06:05.316
- Hey. maggots.
- Hey. Stewart.

77
00:06:06.734 --> 00:06:09.528
What the hell happened to your hair?

78
00:06:09.612 --> 00:06:11.822
You like it?

79
00:06:11.906 --> 00:06:14.074
I just got it cut.

80
00:06:14.158 --> 00:06:17.995
by the most beautiful woman
on the face of God's green earth.

81
00:06:18.078 --> 00:06:20.831
- Looks pretty weird.
- Yeah. thanks.

82
00:06:20.956 --> 00:06:26.670
She called it a European cut.
Says it draws attention away from my ears.

83
00:06:27.379 --> 00:06:29.423
What'd she use? A fuckin' chisel?

84
00:06:29.548 --> 00:06:33.010
Who the hell cares? I tell you.
she's well worth the price of a hat.

85
00:06:33.093 --> 00:06:34.803
She's new. over at Mega Kutz.

86
00:06:34.887 --> 00:06:38.724
I can't trust the opinion of a guy
who scrapes up road kill for a living.

87
00:06:38.807 --> 00:06:41.185
You can trust me with this one.

88
00:06:41.310 --> 00:06:44.104
Man. she got the face of an angel.

89
00:06:44.188 --> 00:06:47.816
Just gives you goose bumps
all over. you know?

90
00:07:45.291 --> 00:07:47.793
Like it? Who's next?

91
00:07:47.877 --> 00:07:50.963
- Uh. right here.
- Come here.

92
00:07:54.216 --> 00:07:56.302
So how do you like it?

93
00:07:57.303 --> 00:07:59.430
Oh. you know. just...

94
00:07:59.513 --> 00:08:02.141
Just like it is. only not quite so long.

95
00:08:02.266 --> 00:08:04.435
So you want it shorter. then?

96
00:08:04.518 --> 00:08:07.855
Yeah. shorter.
I think shorter's the way to go.

97
00:08:16.614 --> 00:08:18.449
So you cut a lot of hair?

98
00:08:19.742 --> 00:08:24.663
I guess so. I mean. I've been working here
a month or so. ever since I moved back.

99
00:08:24.747 --> 00:08:28.334
Oh. so you're not from...
Uh. where are you from?

100
00:08:29.460 --> 00:08:33.714
Oh. I'm from here. I was livin' in Oregon
for a while. Beaver. Oregon.

101
00:08:33.797 --> 00:08:37.718
But then I moved back because
I had to help out with my daddy.

102
00:08:38.594 --> 00:08:41.639
He had stroke number two
and he's paralysed now. so...

103
00:08:42.306 --> 00:08:45.100
That's a... That's a shame. It truly is.

104
00:08:45.184 --> 00:08:49.146
Well. it's his own damn fault.
He's so tense all the time.

105
00:08:50.731 --> 00:08:53.651
It's like he's got fire ants
runnin' through his veins.

106
00:08:53.776 --> 00:08:55.861
Oh. I'm sorry!

107
00:08:59.365 --> 00:09:01.992
How's that. um... I'm sorry.

108
00:09:02.868 --> 00:09:05.454
What did you say your name was?

109
00:09:06.288 --> 00:09:08.332
Actually. I didn't.

110
00:09:09.792 --> 00:09:11.669
It's Gilly.

111
00:09:11.752 --> 00:09:14.630
OK. Gilly. I'm Jo.

112
00:09:14.713 --> 00:09:17.383
Could you hold that there for me?

113
00:09:19.969 --> 00:09:22.680
- How's that for length?
- Beautiful.

114
00:09:25.474 --> 00:09:28.143
So I see you have a cat.

115
00:09:28.227 --> 00:09:33.399
Well. I had a cat. He ran away two weeks ago
and I haven't heard from him since.

116
00:09:33.524 --> 00:09:35.818
Oh. he'll be back. You know cats.

117
00:09:35.943 --> 00:09:40.406
I've had him since he was a pup. I don't know
what I'd do without my little Ringo.

118
00:09:40.489 --> 00:09:45.035
Ringo? That must be a pretty popular
name for a cat these days.

119
00:09:45.119 --> 00:09:46.203
It is?

120
00:09:46.287 --> 00:09:50.583
I work down at the animal shelter and
I just took in a cat yesterday named Ringo.

121
00:09:50.666 --> 00:09:53.252
Too bad this Ringo's missin' a tail.

122
00:09:53.586 --> 00:09:55.588
That's my cat!

123
00:09:55.671 --> 00:10:00.092
- Hey. watch the corner!
- Yeah. yeah. She said put him in ER 4.

124
00:10:07.725 --> 00:10:09.810
Gilly! Are you OK?

125
00:10:10.561 --> 00:10:12.938
Were they able to sew it back on?

126
00:10:13.981 --> 00:10:17.735
No. but they tell me
I'm first in line for an ear donor.

127
00:10:21.197 --> 00:10:23.282
You lying sack!

128
00:10:23.407 --> 00:10:25.993
Well. listen. What are you doin' tonight?

129
00:10:26.076 --> 00:10:28.204
Just healin'. mostly.

130
00:10:28.287 --> 00:10:33.125
Why don't you come over to my house?
I'll cook you dinner and you can bring Ringo.

131
00:10:33.209 --> 00:10:37.671
Listen. Jo. I don't want you to feel you owe
me dinner just because I found your cat

132
00:10:37.755 --> 00:10:40.049
and you cut off my ear.
- I do owe you dinner.

133
00:10:40.132 --> 00:10:44.136
Just say yes. or else I just might
cut off your other ear.

134
00:10:44.220 --> 00:10:48.015
- OK. Uh... 6.30?
- Yeah. 6.30's great.

135
00:10:48.098 --> 00:10:51.185
Don't worry. I'm a much better cook
than I am a hairstylist.

136
00:10:53.646 --> 00:10:57.858
- I just don't know why you're doing this.
- Doin' what?

137
00:10:57.942 --> 00:11:02.154
Cookin' dinner for this fella.
You oughta be fixin' dinner for Jack.

138
00:11:02.238 --> 00:11:06.367
The man who wants to marry you. not some
dog-catcher who makes 18 grand a year

139
00:11:06.450 --> 00:11:09.453
and comes home smellin'
like cat piss every night.

140
00:11:09.578 --> 00:11:12.581
- Promise me you'll be polite.
- Of course I'll be polite.

141
00:11:12.665 --> 00:11:15.459
Of course I'll be polite. Gosh!

142
00:11:17.127 --> 00:11:20.714
Jack called again today.
I talked to him for a long time.

143
00:11:20.839 --> 00:11:22.800
He asked me why you left him.

144
00:11:22.883 --> 00:11:26.387
I wish you would tell him. because
I can't make any sense out of it.

145
00:11:26.720 --> 00:11:28.722
Are you listening to me?

146
00:11:28.806 --> 00:11:32.393
- Hold on.
- Oh. would you... just put the thing down!

147
00:11:33.435 --> 00:11:35.521
You listen to me now.

148
00:11:35.604 --> 00:11:39.650
Good men are few and far between
in this world.

149
00:11:39.733 --> 00:11:44.822
When you find yourself a keeper -
the way I found your sweet pop out there.

150
00:11:44.947 --> 00:11:50.786
then you grab ahold of him and you
treat him the way he wants to be treated.

151
00:11:50.870 --> 00:11:53.205
- Valdine!
- What?

152
00:11:53.330 --> 00:11:55.374
Valdine.

153
00:11:57.877 --> 00:12:00.296
Valdine!

154
00:12:02.882 --> 00:12:07.595
- What is it. gimpy?
- I want a beer. goddammit.

155
00:12:08.721 --> 00:12:13.642
Now. look. You curb your language or I'll take
this Voc-a-lator 3000 right back to Wal-Mart.

156
00:12:13.726 --> 00:12:16.312
You hear me? Jeez!

157
00:12:19.732 --> 00:12:22.443
What in the name of God...

158
00:12:22.526 --> 00:12:25.988
- I was watchin' that.
- Yeah. I bet you were.

159
00:12:26.071 --> 00:12:28.699
You've just had a stroke.
Do you want another one?

160
00:12:28.782 --> 00:12:32.494
- I want you to stay calm.
- Get me a goddamn beer.

161
00:12:41.879 --> 00:12:44.506
Gilly! Ringo!

162
00:12:48.010 --> 00:12:52.806
All the dogs at the animal shelter
chipped in for a little going-away present.

163
00:12:52.890 --> 00:12:55.517
Well. thank them for me. and thank you.

164
00:12:56.560 --> 00:12:59.146
- Just doin' my job.
- How's your ear?

165
00:13:00.731 --> 00:13:03.859
It's OK.
I got all the pus drained out of it.

166
00:13:04.860 --> 00:13:07.613
Close the goddamn door.

167
00:13:08.656 --> 00:13:10.824
You have a robot?

168
00:13:13.327 --> 00:13:15.412
Daddy. I'd like you to meet Gilly Noble.

169
00:13:15.496 --> 00:13:18.415
It's a pleasure to meet you. Mr Wingfield.

170
00:13:20.584 --> 00:13:23.963
He's a little shy around strangers.

171
00:13:24.046 --> 00:13:27.550
- I'm gonna get Ringo some half-and-half.
- OK.

172
00:13:31.679 --> 00:13:33.764
So...

173
00:13:36.267 --> 00:13:38.060
Oh. golf. huh?

174
00:13:38.143 --> 00:13:42.356
It seems every time I play.
I get Tourette's syndrome.

175
00:13:42.398 --> 00:13:44.233
You know. Fore!

176
00:13:44.316 --> 00:13:46.235
Shit. damn. crap.

177
00:13:46.318 --> 00:13:48.237
Fore! Shit. damn. crap.

178
00:13:48.320 --> 00:13:50.573
Hey. dork.

179
00:13:51.240 --> 00:13:53.909
Turn it to Channel 7. dipshit.

180
00:13:56.078 --> 00:13:59.999
You can say "dipshit" with that thing.
That's neat.

181
00:14:00.082 --> 00:14:04.837
Come on. have some more. You probably
don't eat this well very often on your salary.

182
00:14:04.920 --> 00:14:09.133
- Mama. leave him alone.
- Aw. that's OK. Jo.

183
00:14:14.972 --> 00:14:17.141
I'll find room.

184
00:14:17.224 --> 00:14:21.729
So. Willy. what do they pay you
down there for gassin' strays?

185
00:14:21.854 --> 00:14:24.273
No. ma'am. I don't gas them.

186
00:14:24.356 --> 00:14:26.191
What do you do? Hit 'em with a bat?

187
00:14:30.487 --> 00:14:35.284
No. I meant I'm not the one
who actually puts them to sleep.

188
00:14:35.367 --> 00:14:38.662
I. uh... I couldn't do that.

189
00:14:38.746 --> 00:14:44.251
And as for the pay. it's not much.
but it plays into my long-term career goal.

190
00:14:45.169 --> 00:14:48.547
- Which is?
- I wanna be a veterinarian.

191
00:14:48.631 --> 00:14:50.966
You'd be a great vet.

192
00:14:51.050 --> 00:14:53.135
Doctor Noble.

193
00:14:55.137 --> 00:14:58.515
Thanks. but it's not gonna be easy.

194
00:14:58.599 --> 00:15:02.895
Four more years at the junior college
and I'll have my two-year degree.

195
00:15:02.978 --> 00:15:07.441
And then I'll transfer over to State.
and with a BA in general studies

196
00:15:07.524 --> 00:15:12.112
I should be able to get into
any vet school in Mexico.

197
00:15:12.530 --> 00:15:15.032
Sounds foolproof.

198
00:15:15.115 --> 00:15:18.994
If Gilly says he's gonna be a vet.
then I believe he's gonna be a vet.

199
00:15:21.956 --> 00:15:24.208
Excuse me a minute.

200
00:15:32.174 --> 00:15:34.218
Care for a taste of my pie?

201
00:15:35.719 --> 00:15:37.805
No. thanks. I'm full.

202
00:15:39.807 --> 00:15:42.518
Suit yourself. I'm gonna have a slice.

203
00:15:52.194 --> 00:15:55.114
Easy on the corns. Dr Dolittle.

204
00:16:02.872 --> 00:16:04.957
The Lord.

205
00:16:05.624 --> 00:16:07.751
our Lord.

206
00:16:09.086 --> 00:16:15.676
has blessed me with the divine gifts
of tracking. finding and retrieving.

207
00:16:16.093 --> 00:16:19.471
Come on. Vic.
Just tell me what you have so far.

208
00:16:19.555 --> 00:16:21.432
I'll tell you what I got.

209
00:16:23.058 --> 00:16:25.311
Now. I'm about 90 per cent on this.

210
00:16:26.270 --> 00:16:31.525
But I believe that your birth mother is still
alive and living somewhere in the local area.

211
00:16:31.609 --> 00:16:33.694
And her name is...

212
00:16:34.445 --> 00:16:36.530
Suki Yamaguchi.

213
00:16:37.114 --> 00:16:39.200
That sounds a little...

214
00:16:40.242 --> 00:16:42.661
Japanese-y to me.

215
00:16:43.996 --> 00:16:48.584
This detective. Vic Vetter. is lookin'
for my family. But so far. no luck.

216
00:16:48.709 --> 00:16:54.632
What if you find out you're the son of the guy
who invented shoe polish? You'd be rich.

217
00:16:54.715 --> 00:16:57.801
I wouldn't care if he just
shined shoes for a living.

218
00:16:57.885 --> 00:17:01.805
Not havin' a family's left a big.
empty space inside of me.

219
00:17:01.889 --> 00:17:05.142
- It's really important that I find them.
- You will.

220
00:17:07.228 --> 00:17:11.190
This is the first time I've ever
been up here with anyone.

221
00:17:12.358 --> 00:17:16.737
- You don't like it up here. do you?
- No. no. it's fine. It's fine.

222
00:17:19.782 --> 00:17:22.701
Just being here reminds me of a bad time.

223
00:17:24.119 --> 00:17:27.748
I was seven and we had to
put our dog Humpy to sleep.

224
00:17:27.831 --> 00:17:30.209
I still haven't gotten over it.

225
00:17:31.001 --> 00:17:36.090
- It's ridiculous. I know.
- No. that's not ridiculous at all.

226
00:17:36.173 --> 00:17:39.552
Every Friday I see animals
being put to sleep here

227
00:17:39.635 --> 00:17:43.013
and I wish that I could take 'em
all home with me. but I can't.

228
00:17:43.097 --> 00:17:48.435
And every time one of those animals dies.
I feel like a part of me dies too.

229
00:17:49.353 --> 00:17:54.984
About a year ago. I wrote this poem
that I recite to all the dogs before they go.

230
00:17:57.236 --> 00:18:01.782
It helps me and...
I like to think it helps them too.

231
00:18:01.949 --> 00:18:03.784
I'd love to hear it.

232
00:18:03.909 --> 00:18:06.453
No. it's not very good.

233
00:18:06.537 --> 00:18:08.706
I don't care.

234
00:18:08.789 --> 00:18:10.082
OK.

235
00:18:15.546 --> 00:18:17.631
O noble creature

236
00:18:17.715 --> 00:18:19.758
The time has come

237
00:18:19.842 --> 00:18:21.927
For the two of us to part

238
00:18:23.137 --> 00:18:25.431
And for you to go to a better place

239
00:18:26.473 --> 00:18:28.767
A place deep inside my heart

240
00:18:30.311 --> 00:18:32.897
A place where you'll be free to run

241
00:18:32.980 --> 00:18:35.816
After a car or a bouncing ball

242
00:18:37.234 --> 00:18:39.236
So go. noble creature

243
00:18:39.320 --> 00:18:41.405
Through that doggy door

244
00:18:41.989 --> 00:18:45.409
And fetch a stick that's thrown by God

245
00:18:45.492 --> 00:18:48.287
And wag thy tail for ever more

246
00:18:49.955 --> 00:18:52.708
While a friendly voice repeats:

247
00:18:52.833 --> 00:18:55.920
"Good dog. good dog".

248
00:19:00.466 --> 00:19:03.427
So that's it. And after I read it.

249
00:19:03.510 --> 00:19:09.558
I usually fire off a one-gun salute
with a pistol we keep here at the shelter.

250
00:19:12.228 --> 00:19:14.271
I know it sounds silly. but...

251
00:19:17.399 --> 00:19:19.485
It doesn't sound silly.

252
00:20:24.842 --> 00:20:26.886
Help.

253
00:20:27.386 --> 00:20:29.430
Very funny.

254
00:20:57.416 --> 00:21:00.544
This is a great day. It was a good idea.

255
00:21:01.253 --> 00:21:03.547
- Shall we have the champagne?
- No.

256
00:21:04.924 --> 00:21:07.468
Let's wait till later.

257
00:21:07.551 --> 00:21:09.678
You know. the day I cut your ear off.

258
00:21:09.762 --> 00:21:12.598
I never dreamed we'd be
spending six months together.

259
00:21:12.681 --> 00:21:14.683
Yeah. that is pretty funny.

260
00:21:15.851 --> 00:21:19.438
I've had such a good time with you.
just hanging out. having fun.

261
00:21:19.563 --> 00:21:21.732
No strings attached.

262
00:21:21.815 --> 00:21:24.693
Most guys are so possessive.

263
00:21:24.777 --> 00:21:28.447
You know. they talk about marriage
before the first year is even up.

264
00:21:28.531 --> 00:21:33.702
There was this one schmuck. he actually
went out and he got a plane and a banner.

265
00:21:35.829 --> 00:21:38.791
It was so lame! Talk about pressure.

266
00:21:50.678 --> 00:21:53.597
- I'd love to. Gilly.
- Love to what?

267
00:21:53.973 --> 00:21:56.392
I'd love to marry you.

268
00:21:56.475 --> 00:21:59.144
That's my Uncle Joe's plane up there.

269
00:22:01.814 --> 00:22:04.900
Joseph Wingfield is your uncle.

270
00:22:04.984 --> 00:22:07.111
I'm named after him.

271
00:22:07.194 --> 00:22:10.906
You know. it probably
should have occurred to me.

272
00:22:27.423 --> 00:22:29.925
Boy. you don't quit. do ya?

273
00:22:35.514 --> 00:22:37.808
Oh. that's it. That's the spot.

274
00:22:38.642 --> 00:22:42.605
Oh. don't go back there!
We gotta save some for the honeymoon.

275
00:22:42.688 --> 00:22:45.191
What are you sayin'. Gilly?

276
00:22:48.110 --> 00:22:52.364
Nothin'. I was just...
messin' around with Ringo.

277
00:22:58.954 --> 00:23:01.040
Hey. Jo.

278
00:23:01.707 --> 00:23:03.792
Who's Jack?

279
00:23:03.876 --> 00:23:07.546
- What Jack?
- You know.

280
00:23:09.173 --> 00:23:11.467
On-your-ass Jack.

281
00:23:11.550 --> 00:23:15.012
Well. he's my ex-boyfriend from Oregon.

282
00:23:15.095 --> 00:23:18.515
I've been meaning to get it removed.
You're not jealous. are you?

283
00:23:18.599 --> 00:23:22.269
You're the one with the half-naked
Suzanne Somers over his bed.

284
00:23:22.353 --> 00:23:26.482
Come on. Now don't bad-mouth Suzanne.

285
00:23:27.566 --> 00:23:30.486
She got me through
my awkward teenage years.

286
00:23:31.111 --> 00:23:36.450
- Do you mean you beat off to her?
- Not to brag. but... up to five times a day.

287
00:23:36.534 --> 00:23:38.619
Wow.

288
00:23:39.286 --> 00:23:41.956
Do you wanna try to break that record?

289
00:23:48.003 --> 00:23:50.130
Hey. it's Gilly. Leave a message.

290
00:23:50.714 --> 00:23:54.885
Hey. Noble. It's Vic. I know it's early.
but are you there. buddy?

291
00:23:55.886 --> 00:23:58.514
- Pick up. I got a package in the mail.
- I love you. Jo.

292
00:23:58.597 --> 00:24:01.308
- Surprise! I found your mother.
- I love you. Gilly.

293
00:24:01.392 --> 00:24:05.521
I touched all the bases on this one.
I'm 110 per cent sure.

294
00:24:06.480 --> 00:24:10.234
Your mother's name is Valdine Wingfield.

295
00:24:10.317 --> 00:24:12.403
Wingfield.

296
00:24:14.071 --> 00:24:16.240
You gotta understand.

297
00:24:16.323 --> 00:24:19.702
I had just had little Jo
and we were strapped for cash

298
00:24:19.785 --> 00:24:23.747
and then I found out
I was pregnant again - with you!

299
00:24:25.040 --> 00:24:29.587
Old R2-D2 couldn't keep it
in his pants back then.

300
00:24:29.670 --> 00:24:32.381
and now he can't even wipe his own ass!

301
00:24:35.843 --> 00:24:41.265
I just didn't know how I was gonna feed
everybody and you were such a hungry child!

302
00:24:41.348 --> 00:24:44.518
I figured the best thing to do
was to give you away.

303
00:24:44.602 --> 00:24:48.981
You know. to somebody who
wouldn't resent you for your burden.

304
00:24:50.357 --> 00:24:54.320
I mean. one of you had to go
and Jo was already house-broke.

305
00:24:54.862 --> 00:24:56.947
This can't be happening.

306
00:24:57.031 --> 00:25:00.117
I know how difficult this must be for you.

307
00:25:00.201 --> 00:25:03.913
But think how lucky you are that
you found out before it was too late.

308
00:25:03.996 --> 00:25:08.584
before you got married and
consummated this forbidden relationship.

309
00:25:16.300 --> 00:25:18.886
Sweet Lord! You ponied your sister.

310
00:25:22.097 --> 00:25:24.183
Oh. my God.

311
00:25:41.742 --> 00:25:44.703
Hey. maggot. What are you doin' out here?

312
00:25:44.787 --> 00:25:47.081
- Nothin'.
- What you got there?

313
00:25:47.164 --> 00:25:50.543
Well. I'd say Cougar.
What do you think. Wingfield?

314
00:25:52.419 --> 00:25:54.505
It's a coyote. Stewart.

315
00:25:55.756 --> 00:25:58.092
There are no cougars in Indiana.

316
00:25:58.551 --> 00:26:02.346
Hell. I'm talkin' about the car.
Looks like Cougar tread.

317
00:26:02.930 --> 00:26:05.891
- I used to work in a tyre store. you know.
- Yeah?

318
00:26:05.975 --> 00:26:10.646
- Well. I used to work at the animal shelter.
- Hey. Gilly. you know I had no choice.

319
00:26:10.771 --> 00:26:14.441
Know how it feels when newspapers
call you the boss of a sister-fucker?

320
00:26:14.525 --> 00:26:18.320
Whole damn town thinks
I'm runnin' a sister-fuckeria.

321
00:26:18.904 --> 00:26:22.199
Coulda stuck by me. Larry.
It was gonna blow over.

322
00:26:22.283 --> 00:26:24.952
Come on. Gilly. Who are you shittin'?

323
00:26:25.244 --> 00:26:29.832
Not that I blame you. I mean. if I had
a sister that looked like that... whoa!

324
00:26:29.915 --> 00:26:32.167
Wham-bam-thank-you-sis!

325
00:26:32.918 --> 00:26:34.920
You're right about that.

326
00:26:35.004 --> 00:26:41.093
You know. I'd say. sister or no.
I'd still like to get a crack at her.

327
00:26:41.927 --> 00:26:44.221
That is. if she ever comes back.

328
00:26:45.139 --> 00:26:48.225
- Is she still up in Oregon?
- As far as I know.

329
00:26:50.686 --> 00:26:52.313
All right. maggots! Chop chop!

330
00:26:52.438 --> 00:26:55.691
Dearest Gilly. I'm sorry
I left without saying goodbye.

331
00:26:55.816 --> 00:26:58.569
I just couldn't face you
after all that's happened.

332
00:26:58.611 --> 00:27:03.741
The feelings that once seemed so right
became in an instant so wrong.

333
00:27:03.824 --> 00:27:07.328
Though it pains me to say it.
we must never see each other again.

334
00:27:07.411 --> 00:27:10.289
And though we must never
forget the love we shared.

335
00:27:10.372 --> 00:27:14.543
we must. like noble creatures.
move on to another plane.

336
00:27:29.099 --> 00:27:30.768
Valdine?

337
00:27:30.851 --> 00:27:33.270
- Valdine!
- What? I'm busy.

338
00:27:33.354 --> 00:27:35.940
Put lots of salt on that sandwich.

339
00:27:36.023 --> 00:27:38.359
- You want a lot of salt?
- Yes.

340
00:27:48.536 --> 00:27:52.122
- Here you are. honey. Nice and salty.
- Thank you.

341
00:27:57.545 --> 00:27:59.588
Hey. Gilly.

342
00:28:00.464 --> 00:28:02.841
How was your day at work?

343
00:28:02.925 --> 00:28:07.263
I don't know. It was pretty slow.
Just snakes. mostly.

344
00:28:07.972 --> 00:28:12.977
Well. dinner's almost ready.
I made that nice chicken thing you like.

345
00:28:13.561 --> 00:28:17.314
- Hey. Dad.
- I thought you were gonna get a haircut.

346
00:28:17.982 --> 00:28:20.401
Now. Walter. hush.

347
00:28:20.484 --> 00:28:23.988
- Gilly's been through a lot.
- Includin' his own sister.

348
00:28:28.617 --> 00:28:30.703
I'd better get it.

349
00:28:35.040 --> 00:28:37.334
Hello?

350
00:28:37.418 --> 00:28:40.546
Hi. honey. How are you?

351
00:28:41.380 --> 00:28:43.173
How's Jack?

352
00:28:45.467 --> 00:28:47.511
Good. good.

353
00:28:48.053 --> 00:28:50.222
Oh. he's fine.

354
00:28:50.306 --> 00:28:53.434
He's been through a lot.
but he's hanging in there.

355
00:28:53.517 --> 00:28:56.770
I know you miss him. But guess what.

356
00:28:56.854 --> 00:29:00.858
He's regained the use
of both of his arms now.

357
00:29:00.941 --> 00:29:04.820
Both of 'em. You know.
they move every which way.

358
00:29:04.904 --> 00:29:06.822
All right.

359
00:29:06.906 --> 00:29:08.991
OK. well. what is it?

360
00:29:10.618 --> 00:29:14.163
You're getting married?
Oh. Jo-Jo. that is so wonderful!

361
00:29:15.581 --> 00:29:19.210
It's Jo-Jo.
She and Jack are getting married!

362
00:29:19.293 --> 00:29:22.087
Oh. my God. Isn't that wonderful?

363
00:29:22.171 --> 00:29:27.134
Sweetheart. I am really.
really happy for you. I am.

364
00:29:27.259 --> 00:29:31.055
OK. sure.
I'll talk to you tomorrow. Bye-bye.

365
00:29:31.889 --> 00:29:33.349
Yes! Yes!

366
00:29:33.432 --> 00:29:36.810
Sweet Jesus!
The Wingfields have arrived!

367
00:29:39.605 --> 00:29:41.982
I'm rich. I'm rich. uh-huh.

368
00:29:42.066 --> 00:29:44.818
Talkin' to ya. mama! Oh. yeah! Come on!

369
00:29:52.034 --> 00:29:54.328
- Pervert!
- Gilly. how's your sister?

370
00:29:59.500 --> 00:30:02.836
Jo knew you'd understand why
she couldn't possibly invite you.

371
00:30:02.920 --> 00:30:06.715
- I know.
- I think you should be happy for your sister.

372
00:30:06.799 --> 00:30:10.135
Oh. hell. After what you put her through.

373
00:30:10.219 --> 00:30:14.765
it's a wonder she didn't quit the sausage
and become a vaginatarian.

374
00:30:14.848 --> 00:30:16.392
Oh. good God.

375
00:30:16.517 --> 00:30:19.937
Gilly. listen. Things are
really looking up for her.

376
00:30:20.020 --> 00:30:23.899
She's got a little beauty parlour up there
and a guy who's crazy about her

377
00:30:23.983 --> 00:30:27.236
and. quite frankly.
a millionaire several times over.

378
00:30:27.319 --> 00:30:32.157
Quit babying the boy. Valdine.
He banged his own sister. for Christ's sakes.

379
00:30:32.241 --> 00:30:34.743
What do you want? To give him a medal?

380
00:30:34.869 --> 00:30:39.623
Listen to me. This could be a whole new start
for us all. so I want you to keep your chin up.

381
00:30:39.707 --> 00:30:44.545
Do you know what the Bible says
about fuckin' your own sister?

382
00:30:44.628 --> 00:30:47.131
- Don't!
- Hush up. droopy.

383
00:30:47.798 --> 00:30:51.510
He's my baby. my precious gift from God.

384
00:30:53.470 --> 00:30:58.100
I'll get it. I baked you some ginger snaps.
They're cooling on the stove.

385
00:30:59.643 --> 00:31:03.856
- What do you want?
- Sorry to bother you. Mrs Wingfield.

386
00:31:03.981 --> 00:31:07.443
- My name is Leon Pitofsky.
- Oh. my God.

387
00:31:07.526 --> 00:31:09.528
- Did I come at a bad time?
- No.

388
00:31:10.738 --> 00:31:17.161
It's just... you look remarkably like my dear
husband when he was a much younger man.

389
00:31:18.120 --> 00:31:21.207
Well. that stands to reason. ma'am.

390
00:31:23.500 --> 00:31:25.669
Look at this.

391
00:31:25.794 --> 00:31:30.466
It's all there. Blood tests.
hospital records. DNA.

392
00:31:30.549 --> 00:31:34.428
Look. Here's your signature.
givin' up your rights to me.

393
00:31:35.304 --> 00:31:37.389
Oh. my Lord.

394
00:31:37.765 --> 00:31:39.850
Then it's true.

395
00:31:39.934 --> 00:31:41.769
You are my son.

396
00:31:41.852 --> 00:31:44.188
I've finally found you. Mama!

397
00:31:46.148 --> 00:31:50.694
Well. if he's your son.
then who the hell's this sack of shit?

398
00:31:53.822 --> 00:31:56.367
I'll tell you who he is. He's a grifter.

399
00:31:56.450 --> 00:32:00.120
He's a shyster that's been freeloading
in this house for a solid year!

400
00:32:00.204 --> 00:32:02.498
- Oh. wait. Mom...
- I knew it!

401
00:32:02.581 --> 00:32:05.251
Get outta my house. you goddamn hippie!

402
00:32:05.334 --> 00:32:07.711
Hippie? Whoa. hold on.

403
00:32:07.795 --> 00:32:10.589
Walter. get that impostor outta here.

404
00:32:10.673 --> 00:32:13.259
- Dad. relax.
- Hey. buddy. you heard my mama.

405
00:32:13.342 --> 00:32:15.427
Now get the hell out.

406
00:32:17.805 --> 00:32:20.474
Get your hands off my daddy. you bastard!

407
00:32:22.309 --> 00:32:25.646
- Walter! He's havin' another stroke.
- Dad. what's the problem?

408
00:32:25.729 --> 00:32:29.441
Call 911. My God! You! You can get the...

409
00:32:29.567 --> 00:32:32.403
Get the police!
I'll have this grifter arrested!

410
00:32:32.862 --> 00:32:35.030
- Police.
- Get an ambulance!

411
00:34:07.456 --> 00:34:09.542
Oh. my God.

412
00:34:11.085 --> 00:34:13.170
Oh. shit.

413
00:34:15.631 --> 00:34:17.675
Hey! Mr Magoo!

414
00:34:17.758 --> 00:34:21.762
You knocked my freakin' legs off. daddy.
Were you even lookin' at the road?

415
00:34:21.845 --> 00:34:25.307
I'm sorry. I've never hit anyone before.

416
00:34:25.391 --> 00:34:28.060
Well. I'm glad to be your first.
Hope I was gentle.

417
00:34:28.185 --> 00:34:31.105
Now. be a friend and fetch
my getaway sticks. daddy.

418
00:34:31.230 --> 00:34:35.901
- Your what? What do you...
- My legs. captain. my legs!

419
00:34:36.527 --> 00:34:37.611
Oh. shit.

420
00:34:37.695 --> 00:34:41.824
Less faeces. more fetchin'.
Get over here and get it. boy.

421
00:34:45.536 --> 00:34:49.874
I gotta straighten this damn thing.
It's bent all to hell.

422
00:34:49.957 --> 00:34:52.376
- Watch out. watch out.
- Watch out?

423
00:34:52.459 --> 00:34:56.005
Boy. that is a hell of a thing
for you to say to me.

424
00:35:00.759 --> 00:35:03.846
Well. in all fairness.
you were in the middle of the road.

425
00:35:03.929 --> 00:35:08.642
How else was I supposed to flag you down?
I was a desperate man.

426
00:35:08.726 --> 00:35:13.814
Another 20 minutes and them bloodthirsty
mosquitoes woulda sucked me dry.

427
00:35:13.898 --> 00:35:17.943
- How long have you been out here?
- Oh. about two hours.

428
00:35:18.569 --> 00:35:22.156
My airplane ran outta gas.
I had to land in a clearing.

429
00:35:22.239 --> 00:35:26.368
- You're a pilot?
- You're goddamn right I'm a pilot.

430
00:35:26.452 --> 00:35:28.495
My card. right there.

431
00:35:29.163 --> 00:35:31.749
- "The Big Dig"?
- That's right.

432
00:35:32.750 --> 00:35:37.046
Dig McCaffrey. I make a lotta coin
flyin' those gigs nobody else wants.

433
00:35:37.129 --> 00:35:42.218
Take sportsmen out to the bush. fly banners
over supermarket openings. crop-dustin'.

434
00:35:42.301 --> 00:35:44.720
I'll fly up your ass if the money's right.

435
00:35:44.803 --> 00:35:48.390
Hey. that's pretty good. Do you think
I oughta put that on my card?

436
00:35:48.474 --> 00:35:52.853
- So where am I takin' you?
- As close to Beaver as you can get.

437
00:35:52.937 --> 00:35:58.150
And a man as sexy and fertile as me
likes to stay close to the beaver.

438
00:35:58.609 --> 00:36:02.238
- That's a good one!
- That's right where I'm headed.

439
00:36:02.321 --> 00:36:07.743
Say. you look like you're draggin' there.
chief. Why don't you let me drive?

440
00:36:07.826 --> 00:36:10.204
- Oh. no. that's fine.
- I'm wired.

441
00:36:10.287 --> 00:36:13.791
Nothin' like gettin' bounced off a bumper
to put a cat on full tilt.

442
00:36:14.750 --> 00:36:17.711
So. where's your launch pad. Kerouac?

443
00:36:17.795 --> 00:36:21.924
- My what?
- Where you from. baby? Where you from?

444
00:36:23.509 --> 00:36:26.178
- I'm from Indiana.
- You remind me of a fella I knew

445
00:36:26.262 --> 00:36:29.431
down in El Paso durin'
my import-export days.

446
00:36:30.015 --> 00:36:31.934
Never been there.

447
00:36:32.017 --> 00:36:34.311
So. who's the skirt?

448
00:36:34.395 --> 00:36:38.107
- How did you know that I was...
- Dig knows many things. baby.

449
00:36:38.190 --> 00:36:42.319
Plus you got that look of a man with
a diamond engagement ring on his pinkie.

450
00:36:42.403 --> 00:36:46.574
Oh. yeah. About a year ago.
she was the love of my life.

451
00:36:48.450 --> 00:36:51.453
Then I found out she was my sister.

452
00:36:51.537 --> 00:36:53.914
Then. about three days ago...

453
00:36:55.416 --> 00:36:56.917
Dig! Dig!

454
00:37:03.549 --> 00:37:07.344
Just a little case of the white-line fever.
that's all. baby!

455
00:37:07.428 --> 00:37:11.432
Dig just needs a little music.
Rock and roll. baby!

456
00:37:11.515 --> 00:37:15.978
I'd like to see somebody fall asleep
to this shit here. Ted Nugent!

457
00:37:26.488 --> 00:37:28.532
Hey. Dig!

